    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="750"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–2645</note>
                <head>No. 750<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the Soviet Delegation</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d750fn1">Discussed at the Third Meeting of the Subcommittee
                        on Implementation of the Yalta Declaration on Liberated Europe, July 26. See
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_418">p. 418</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation?]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-26">July 26,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Proposed Soviet Redraft of Paragraph</hi> 2 <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">of the Paper on Liberated Europe</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >Freedom of the Press</hi>)</p>
                <p>The Conference takes note of the fact that now the representatives of the press
                    of the Allied countries in the countries liberated from German invaders have
                    received the opportunity to work in normal conditions and to describe on a large
                    scale in the press the situation in these countries.</p>
                <p>At the same time in view of the termination of the <gloss target="#t_War1"
                        >war</gloss> in Europe conditions have been created which permit to grant
                    greater facilities for the work of the representatives of the allied press in
                    the countries <pb facs="0843" n="649" xml:id="pg_649"/> with which armistice
                    agreements have been concluded, provided the interests of the security of allied
                    occupational forces in these countries be observed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
